    dc:creator "Aona, Lidyanne Yuriko Saleme", "Silva, Marcos José Da" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "A beautiful new species of Dichorisandra (Commelinaceae) from the mountains of northeastern Goiás, Brazil" ;
    bibo:endPage "224" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Phytotaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-10-17" ;
    bibo:startPage "216" ;
    bibo:volume "620" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012398>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012400>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012402> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012398>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Dichorisandra pulcherrima M.J.Silva & Aona. A. Fertile branch. B. Leaf. C. Detail of the leaf base. D. Sheath, note the dense trichomes. E. Trichomes on the adaxial surface of the leaf. F. Trichomes on the abaxial surface of the leaf. G. Inflorescence detail. H. Floral bud. I. Cincinnus bracts. J. Detail of trichomes on the adaxial side of the cincinnus bract. K. Bracteole. L. Detail of the trichomes on the adaxial side of the bracteole. M. Flower in ventral view. N. Sepals. O. Sepal trichomes, adaxial view. P. Petals, adaxial view. Q. Androecium and gynoecium. R. Gynoecium with two stamens removed. S. Stamens. T. Detail of the stigma. U. Fruit. (From holotype, Illustrated by Cristiano Gualberto)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10012398/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012400>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Dichorisandra pulcherrima M.J.Silva & Aona. A. Habit. B. Portion of the stem densely hairy. C. Sheath, note the tomentose ferrugineous trichomes. D. Underground system, note the fascicled roots tubers. E. Inflorescence. F. Flower in frontal view. G. Fruit, note surface verrucose. G. Open fruit, note the orange aril (Images by M.J. Silva)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10012400/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012402>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Dichorisandra pulcherrima M.J.Silva & Aona in Goiás state, Midwestern region of Brazil. A. Map of Brazil, highlighting Goiás State in gray; B. Map for the state of Goiás, showing its political boundaries and variation in elevation. C. Municipality of Niquelândia (dotted area) with the species distribution points. Abbreviations for the Brazilian states (BA, Bahia; GO, Goiás; MG, Minas Gerais; MS, Mato Grosso do Sul; MT, Mato Grosso; TO, Tocantins) and the Distrito Federal (DF)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10012402/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

